12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,080
80 million.

13
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:40,680
90 million.

14
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,840
120 million.

15
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,320
200 million.

16
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,520
210 million.

17
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:52,800
300 million.

18
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,000
Someone bids 300 million.

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,640
Any higher?

20
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:00,160
Okay.

21
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,400
Sold.

22
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,600
Congratulations to the president of the Times Group,

23
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,800
Zhen Shidai, Mr. Zhen.

24
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:11,800
Mr. Zhen,

25
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:12,960
The Zhen Shidai Charity Foundation

26
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,640
operated by your group

27
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,600
has always been dedicated to social welfare.

28
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:17,280
A year ago,

29
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:19,120
Hao Feng committed suicide at the Black Gold Hotel.

30
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,640
His fund went bankrupt.

31
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:21,520
As an investor,

32
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:23,040
do you bear some responsibility?

33
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,600
Out of appreciation for Hao Feng's talent

34
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,840
and the hope that memory technology

35
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,000
could help more people

36
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,160
suffering from brain diseases,

37
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:33,600
I provided Hao Feng

38
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,000
with some funding.

39
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,720
I'm also a victim.

40
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,680
I haven't got my money back

41
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:41,240
yet.

42
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,720
Are you really unaware of the fact

43
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:43,640
that you concealed the failure

44
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,720
of Hao Feng's experiment?

45
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,400
Mr. Zhen,

46
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,680
the public opinion has...

47
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,160
Excuse me.

48
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,440
Has the bidding started?

49
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,560
Yes.

50
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,840
I was just about to remind you.

51
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,040
Today's schedule is indeed quite full.

52
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,520
Sorry.

53
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,400
Excuse me.

54
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,000
Mr. Zhen.

55
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:58,600
Please wait a moment.

56
00:01:59,360 --> 00:01:59,960
Mr. Zhen.

57
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,320
You...

58
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,080
You are here today to report on the Times Gallery.

59
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:03,600
Follow me.

60
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,800
This way, please.

61
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,480
My brother poured his heart and soul

62
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,240
into pursuing scientific research,

63
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,960
but Zhen Shidai

64
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,400
twisted it into a scam.

65
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:20,880
Those victims

66
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,000
hated the wrong person.

67
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,320
My brother's name

68
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,360
and his scientific ideals

69
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,280
were trampled into the mud.

70
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,600
He was too powerful

71
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,400
and hid too deep.

72
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,600
He smeared Hao Feng.

73
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,840
He did it flawlessly,

74
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,400
but at least we know the truth.

75
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,360
Zhen Shida has been embezzling money for years,

76
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,400
and he's been using some of it to invest in paintings.

77
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,920
This appreciates much faster

78
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,480
than keeping it in the bank.

79
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,560
Do you have a plan?

80
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,120
Come with me.

81
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,760
Our first step

82
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:01,480
is to take down the entire Times Gallery.

83
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,920
Actually, the place you're in now

84
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,480
is the main exhibition hall

85
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:17,280
for the exhibition.

86
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:18,040
Okay.

87
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,000
No more questions.

88
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:19,800
This way, please.

89
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,360
Okay, goodbye.

90
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,440
Hello, sir.

91
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,240
How can I help you?

92
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,560
Mr. Ye Zhiqiu.

93
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,440
I've heard so much about you.

94
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:44,320
I'm James,

95
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:45,560
an independent curator.

96
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:48,120
I just returned from RCAA.

97
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,440
Your collection here

98
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,160
is truly impressive.

99
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,040
James,

100
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:55,880
nice to meet you.

101
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,000
RCAA,

102
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,480
the Royal Ceylon College of Arts,

103
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,600
has indeed produced many

104
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:03,520
outstanding talents.

105
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,360
Among the entire gallery,

106
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,880
my favorite piece

107
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,240
is still Disappearing Roses.

108
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,160
As the most valuable piece

109
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,360
in the gallery,

110
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,880
it's naturally

111
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,279
the most valued by most people.

112
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:22,320
Just like the gallery's logo,

113
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,560
it carries an implied artistic charm.

114
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,240
Though with just a few strokes,

115
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,440
you can feel

116
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,120
the creator's

117
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,520
focus isn't on realism or technical skill,

118
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,160
but on the essence and spirit.

119
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,680
However...

120
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,320
However, what?

121
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,160
Black and white as the base color

122
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,080
symbolize a kind of balance.

123
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:42,040
If you want to strengthen this balance,

124
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,240
you need a beam of light.

125
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:55,040
I didn't expect you to have

126
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,320
such a taste in art.

127
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,280
I'm just a beginner.

128
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,680
Actually, I still have a lot of questions

129
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,880
to discuss with you.

130
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,040
I happen to be free today.

131
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,680
Let's talk in my office.

132
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,320
This way.

133
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,320
To be honest,

134
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,600
I did design

135
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,840
the logo for the gallery.

136
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,800
I knew I wasn't wrong about you.

137
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,520
Mr. Ye,

138
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,200
I know

139
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,960
you're not just an art expert,

140
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,880
but also a talented artist.

141
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,960
I'm not sure

142
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,720
if I should say this,

143
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,720
but it's okay.

144
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,400
Designing a logo is

145
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,600
to design a logo.

146
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,280
Yeah.

147
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,120
I've been

148
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,440
managing the gallery for the past two years.

149
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,560
I have a question

150
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,600
about the gallery

151
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,640
that I'd like to discuss with you.

152
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,640
I'm coming.

153
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,640
Mr. Ye,

154
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,600
long time no see.

155
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,400
Okay.

156
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,880
Today,

157
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,560
I'm here to seek revenge.

158
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,560
You took my Black Diamond Heart.

159
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,880
You must compensate me with several paintings.

160
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,560
What are you talking about, Mr. Zhang?

161
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,440
This Black Diamond Heart

162
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,160
was bought by Mr. Zhen

163
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,880
for a solid 300 million.

164
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,200
How can it be called a theft?

165
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,400
I don't care.

166
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,360
I like it.

167
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,400
Then it's mine.

168
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,880
How about this?

169
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:27,800
You help me pick out some paintings.

170
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,840
Choose a few paintings.

171
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,360
Mr. Zhang.

172
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,120
Today I...

173
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,200
Look at me...

174
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:35,800
Sorry.

175
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,080
I forgot to introduce him to you.

176
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,560
This is Mr. Zhang,

177
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,920
the young master of Zhang Group.

178
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,920
Hello.

179
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,800
James.

180
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,120
He just graduated from RCAA last year.

181
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,200
I'm a newcomer in the field of curating.

182
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:48,480
I'm here today to learn from Ms. Ye.

183
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:50,800
Ms. Ye,

184
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,360
you've collected so many good paintings

185
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,640
for Zhen Shidai.

186
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,920
Our Zhang's Group

187
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,840
also has galleries abroad.

188
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,040
How about this?

189
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,240
Please help me

190
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,040
pick out a few paintings

191
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,000
from some famous artists.

192
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,520
I'll take them all.

193
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:04,280
Price

194
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:04,640
is negotiable.

195
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,400
Mr. Zhang,

196
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,800
it's like this.

197
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,360
Collecting art

198
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,240
is not just a simple transaction.

199
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:15,480
It's more about the connection we have with it,

200
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,000
our appreciation and recognition of it.

201
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:19,760
In that case,

202
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,360
your mindset

203
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,600
is not suitable for collecting.

204
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,040
RCAA, right?

205
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,240
I know someone there.

206
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:32,680
Hello?

207
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,440
Adam?

208
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,840
Yeah, it's Zhang.

209
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,400
I need to ask you something.

210
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,840
Was there a graduate from your school last year

211
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:42,720
named James?

212
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,920
James?

213
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:46,960
Never heard of him.

214
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,640
Are you sure?

215
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,880
I'm the president of the student council.

216
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,120
Of course, I'm sure.

217
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,320
Alright, you can go now.

218
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,080
Mr. Ye,

219
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,360
I can't find any record of this person.

220
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,640
So, this person's credentials...

221
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:06,920
Could it be...

222
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,800
What does this mean?

223
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:13,840
Yes, Mr. Ye,

224
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,160
my credentials are fake.

225
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,160
See?

226
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,000
I never attended

227
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,520
Royal College of Ceylon.

228
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,800
I told you so.

229
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,520
Fake!

230
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,720
Liar, big liar!

231
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,000
Mr. Ye told me, didn't he?

232
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,000
I caught you faking your credentials.

233
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,760
See, Mr. Ye.

234
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,720
I know

235
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,840
this industry values pedigree

236
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,960
and credentials.

237
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,360
To get things done

238
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,640
in this circle,

239
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,520
sometimes I had to resort to this.

240
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,920
But in reality,

241
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,040
I also detest

242
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,200
my own behavior.

243
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:49,320
Ms. Ye,

244
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,640
if you think I've deceived you,

245
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,240
I apologize.

246
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:54,880
I'm sorry.

247
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:00,680
Wait a minute.

248
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,040
Here's the personal information you wanted.

249
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,080
Although this Ye Zhiqiu

250
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:12,120
seems glamorous on the surface,

251
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,560
he was just an ordinary person before,

252
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,920
unsuccessful and frustrated.

253
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,600
never attended a prestigious school,

254
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,160
never had a renowned mentor,

255
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,640
and has always made a living by selling paintings.

256
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,240
But business wasn't good.

257
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,720
He worked at a gallery to make ends meet

258
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,080
and gradually climbed his way

259
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,640
to the position of manager at the Times Gallery.

260
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,760
His journey was quite tough.

261
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,880
Then I'll empathize with him.

262
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:44,440
What do you want to do?

263
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,960
What I want to do

264
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,920
is to help those

265
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,800
who are shut out of the art circle,

266
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,360
and make their works

267
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,600
recognized

268
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,520
and seen.

269
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:56,760
I admit

270
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,920
my education is fake,

271
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,280
but my identity as a curator

272
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,120
is not fake.

273
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,320
Actually, I'm here

274
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,560
to cooperate

275
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,520
with the most influential art salon in the city,

276
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:07,480
He's Art Gallery,

277
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,840
and the Times Art Gallery

278
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,600
to jointly organize a

279
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,040
collection exhibition.

280
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,760
The paintings from the Times Art Gallery

281
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,280
have always been

282
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:19,080
personal collections of Mr. Zhen.

283
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,760
This is not something I can decide on my own.

284
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:22,960
Sorry.

285
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,560
Exactly.

286
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,320
Such valuable paintings.

287
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,080
If something goes wrong

288
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,320
during borrowing,

289
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,240
who's gonna take the blame?

290
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,080
Mr. Ye,

291
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,480
I understand your concerns.

292
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,320
But this time, it's a rare opportunity.

293
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,360
It's the son of the He Art Gallery's director,

294
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,080
He Xiaochen.

295
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,400
He told me

296
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,680
he's particularly interested

297
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,800
in the paintings from our gallery.

298
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,480
You know He Xiaochen?

299
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,160
I heard he's been staying

300
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:50,400
at the Hejin Hotel these days,

301
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,040
He's here for the annual

302
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,280
Go tournament.

303
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:54,360
I know He too.

304
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,160
I heard he's very eccentric,

305
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,200
hard to get close to,

306
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,400
and only cares about playing Go.

307
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:00,520
Yes.

308
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,360
I've heard that too.

309
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,840
He

310
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,400
is somewhat aloof and proud.

311
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,880
Is he very aloof?

312
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,400
I don't think so.

313
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,680
The guest in room 1909

314
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,240
is allergic to eggs.

315
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,320
We need to make another one.

316
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,480
Okay, hurry up.

317
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,840
My chess game was solved.
